<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - ASSEMBLE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Except for the PTO gears, the upper and lower countershaft assemblies are the same. To avoid confusion
            during installation, mark the upper countershaft (45-tooth PTO gear) with a "U". The lower countershaft has
            a 47-tooth PTO gear.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the roll pin and key in countershaft keyway.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align 3rd speed gear keyway with the countershaft key and press the gear on the countershaft
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017e1">Figure 141</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017e1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017e1" filename="../figg13/g13017e1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 141. 3rd Speed Gear Keyway</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align PTO gear keyway with the countershaft key and press the gear on the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017e2">Figure 142</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017e2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017e2" filename="../figg13/g13017e2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 142. PTO Gear Keyway</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align drive gear keyway with the countershaft key and press the gear on the countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017e3">Figure 143</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017e3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017e3" filename="../figg13/g13017e3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 143. Drive Gear Keyway</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear retaining snap ring on each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017e4">Figure 144</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017e4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017e4" filename="../figg13/g13017e4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 144. Drive Gear Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-driver or a press to install the bearing inner race on the countershaft
                against the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017e4">Figure 144</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
